title: Nevada women’s golf 7th at Aggie Invitational
text:
Nevada women’s golf 7th at Aggie Invitational Staff report 5:32 p.m. PDT October 7, 2015 (Photo: McGibboney, Ian) CONNECT 5 TWEET LINKEDIN COMMENT EMAIL MORE 
LAS CRUCES, N.M. – Senior Caryn Khoo took fourth place and led the Nevada women’s golf team to a seventh-place finish at the Aggie Invitational on Wednesday. 
Khoo opened the day one shot off the lead but opened with back-to-back bogeys to start her round on Wednesday. She finished the day with a 75 and 1 under for the tournament. 
NMSU’s Viviana Macias held on for the individual title at 6 under. BYU edged NMSU for the team title. Nevada was seventh, three shots back of Mountain West foe Boise State. 
Celyn Khoo led the Pack in round three with a 73 and moved up to a tie for 22nd overall, one shot ahead of Bertille Dupont. Kaitlin Collom finished tied for 46th after a 76 on Wednesday and Chaithra Katamneni was 59th. 
Nevada returns to action in two weeks at the Las Vegas Collegiate Showdown in Boulder City. Read or Share this story: http://on.rgj.com/1LiRN2p TOP VIDEOS
